    },
    {
      "id": "5cc95bc9ff2d09a449e06e29857b1e779a8846a3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 257,
        "name": "Keith Mannthey",
        "email": "keith.mannthey@intel.com",
        "username": "kmannth",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-06-11 01:13:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\nThe OSTs not being used is a real issue as the lproc subsystem does not present 0 values. I had played with having a roc_hit_init call at the start of every function that used roc_hit that would do a write/read on every OST but it seemed heavy weight.\n\nI looked at using snapshot_time but that lead to some other issue with ltcl.  Is there a proper way to say \"Are the lproc values I want going to be present\" ? \n\nlproc not reporting a stable format is a bit of a tricky thing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
